{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n\nAgents get confused about which code the completion verifier reviews on close. The\nclose gate runs `verify_completion` with `ref=\"HEAD\", fetch=False, repo_root=<the\ncheckout the command runs from>` (`src/rebar/_commands/transition_close.py:183`), so it\nverifies the committed `HEAD` of **whichever checkout the `transition … closed` command is\nrun from** — NOT `origin/main`, and NOT necessarily the worktree where the edits were made.\nThe observed failure mode: an agent edits in a worktree but runs the close from the root of\nthe main checkout, so the verifier reads the wrong (unchanged) tree.\n\n## What\n\nTwo coordinated changes (do not add meta-commentary framing them as \"defense in depth\" —\nagents only need the actionable behavior):\n\n1. **Document the behavior factually** — make the docs state that the close-gate verifier\n   reviews the committed `HEAD` of the checkout the close command runs from, and that you\n   must run close from the worktree/branch that holds the code to be verified.\n2. **Fix the guidance** — repo rules and the two agent skills must instruct the agent to\n   `cd` into the worktree it creates and run all subsequent commands (edits, gates, rebar,\n   close, git) from inside it.\n\n## Scope\n\n- `docs/repo-snapshot-gates.md` — close-gate sentence + reconcile the \"cwd/branch decoupling\"\n  statement so `ref=HEAD` (the CLI close path) reads as resolved relative to the invoking\n  checkout.\n- `docs/llm-framework.md` — the close-gate section.\n- `CLAUDE.md` — completion-verifier/close-gate guidance; and the \"work in a fresh worktree\"\n  guidance (add the `cd`-into-worktree instruction).\n- `CLAUDE.local.md` (local-only; not committed) — worktree guidance.\n- `examples/claude-skills/rebar-implement/SKILL.md` and\n  `examples/claude-skills/rebar-debug/SKILL.md` — the worktree-creation step.\n\nOut of scope (kept lean): reconciling ADR-0005's decoupling note is optional; MCP/CLI\ndocstring one-liners are secondary and would trip the reference-doc drift gate.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `docs/repo-snapshot-gates.md` states the close gate verifies the committed `HEAD` of\n      the checkout/worktree the `transition … closed` command runs from (not `origin/main`,\n      not the main checkout), and directs running close from the worktree holding the code.\n- [ ] `docs/repo-snapshot-gates.md`'s \"cwd/branch decoupling\" statement is reconciled so it\n      no longer reads as contradicting the `ref=HEAD` close path (HEAD is resolved relative\n      to the invoking checkout).\n- [ ] `docs/llm-framework.md` close-gate section notes the verifier reads the committed\n      `HEAD` of the checkout the close command runs from.\n- [ ] `CLAUDE.md` completion-verifier/close-gate guidance tells the agent to run close from\n      the worktree/branch that contains the code to be verified.\n- [ ] `CLAUDE.md` \"work in a fresh worktree\" guidance instructs the agent to `cd` into the\n      worktree and run all subsequent commands from inside it.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] `CLAUDE.local.md` (local-only, git-ignored — not in the committed\n      tree, so not codebase-verifiable) worktree guidance instructs the agent to `cd` into the\n      created worktree and run all subsequent commands from inside it, consistent with the\n      `CLAUDE.md` instruction.\n- [ ] `examples/claude-skills/rebar-implement/SKILL.md` Phase 1 instructs the agent to `cd`\n      into the created worktree and run subsequent commands from there.\n- [ ] `examples/claude-skills/rebar-debug/SKILL.md` worktree step instructs the agent to\n      `cd` into the created worktree and run subsequent commands from there.\n- [ ] The B-layer edits (rules + skills) are plain operational instructions; they do NOT\n      explain a \"defense in depth\" rationale.\n- [ ] `make lint` passes on the change."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783919713308346001,"uuid":"c590bbe8-f8eb-4439-8b93-2c645dac7970"}